The paper deals with counting problems on digraphs and introduces a new concept of z-topological orderings for digraphs. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the relationship between z-topological orderability and other digraph width measures, which could fall under Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper's focus on counting problems and graph families with arbitrarily large tree-width and clique width could also place it in the Combinatorics (cs.CC) sub-category.
